text: The Cathedral Church of Saint Mary in Murcia (), commonly called the Cathedral of Murcia, is a church in Murcia, Spain. It is the only cathedral in use in the Roman Catholic Diocese of Cartagena in Spain. The Cathedral Church of Saint Mary in Murcia was one of 100 finalists for the 12 Treasures of Spain in 2007. ==References== ==Other websites== Category:Roman Catholic cathedrals in Spain Category:12 Treasures of Spain - Finalists Category:Murcia Category:14th-century buildings and structures
